    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.	Number of death arising from priority natural hazard events (flood and drought)
2.	Total economic losses (in GHS amount) attributed to priority natural hazard events (flood and drought)
3.	Number of people affected (evacuated, provided with aid) by priority natural hazard events (flood and drought)
4.	Number and timeliness of EW issued/ communicated per disaster in a year or season
5.	Number of hazards that had EW issued and acted upon to ensure safety
6.	Systems are in place to gather data, analyze, develop and communicate early warning information on priority hazards 
7.	People-centered and multi-stakeholder involved EWS are in place for all major hazards, with outreach to communities.
8.	National and district-level risk assessments information exist for priority hazards (flood and drought) in Ghana
9.	A systematic, standardized process to collect, assess and share data, maps and trends on hazard vulnerabilities are established 
10.	Number of people and/or groups who know and understand hazard risks of priority hazards
11.	Number of groups and/or communities implementing hazard risk reduction interventions
12.	Number of maps produces or updated
13.	A systematic, standardized process to collect, assess and share data, maps and trends on hazard vulnerabilities are established 
14.	An effective hazard monitoring and warning service with a sound scientific and technical basis is established 
15.	Communication and dissemination systems to ensure people and communities are warned in advance of implementing natural hazard events and facilitate national and regional coordination and information exchange are developed
16.	The ability of communities to respond to natural disasters through enhanced education of natural hazard risks, EWS, community participation and disaster preparedness is strengthened
17.	Institutional, legislative and policy frameworks and engagements that support the implementation and maintenance of effective early warning systems are developed
18.	N</narrative>
    </description>
